  "texts": [
    "The probability is determined based on the training dataset.",
    "ChatGPT-3, for example, was trained on nearly 500 billion tokens of text to very accurately predict which word to put next [4].",
    "In addition, it knows style and grammar to be able to construct correct sentences.",
    "This way of probabilistic \"thinking\", however, is prone to errors, as the most likely text completion is not always the correct answer [15,25].Coming back to the question of what it can't do, the answer lies with deterministic modelling.",
    "Contrary to a probabilistic model, which incorporates probability and randomness, the output of a deterministic model is determined in its entirety by the input values and parameter settings [28]."
  ],
